                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d781">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">819.52G31/24: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Flexer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-03T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 3, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. Referring to the Legation’s number 57, July 2, 3 p.m. Dr. Garay informed me
                    this morning that he telegraphed to Panaman Consul General, New York following
                    our conversation instructing that Elliott be informed that sale or alienation of
                    Pinas Bay properties must have prior approval of Panaman Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Flexer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
